2οΈβƒ£ What's happening in the background with React?

β— We updated the state => React updated the view                                      _______________ 
  β–  How can you update an HTML element?                                              β½  Virtual DOM  βΎ
    β—‹ A HTML page is represented by DOM(Document Object Model)                        β€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύ
    β—‹ Each element in a HTML page is a node in the DOM                               /diff&update    β†– creates
    β—‹ You need to update the DOM to update the element                             β†™                   \
    β—‹ HOWEVER, writing code to update the DOM can be complex and slow!         __________  events __________
  β–  React takes a different approach:                                         β½   DOM    βΎ  γ…΅β†’  β½   App    βΎ
    β—‹ Virtual DOM: "virtual" representation of a UI (kept in memory)           β€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύ         β€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύβ€Ύ
      β—¦ React code updates Virtual DOM
    β—‹ React identifies changes and synchronizes them to HTML page
      β—¦ 1: React creates Virtual DOM v1 on load of page
      β—¦ 2: You perform an action
        β–« 3: React creates Virtual DOM v2 as a result of your action
        β–« 4: React performs a diff between v1 and v2
        β–« 5: React synchronizes changes (updates HTML page) 
β— Summary: We are NOT updating the DOM directly!
  β–  React identifies changes and efficiently updates the DOM

β— React takes a different approach:
ν•μ§€λ§ λ¦¬μ•΅νΈλ” μ΄κ²ƒκ³Ό μ™„μ „ν λ‹¤λ¥Έ λ°©μ‹μΌλ΅ λ™μ‘ν•λ‹¤
    β—‹ Virtual DOM: "virtual" representation of a UI (kept in memory) 
λ¦¬μ•΅νΈλ” 'κ°€μƒ DOM (Virtual DOM)'μ΄λΌλ” κ±Έ μ‚¬μ©ν•λ‹¤
